Unauthorized charges, deceptive practices, and subscription fraud
This company operates using deceptive and fraudulent practices.
Without my consent, without a signed agreement, and without any clear authorization, KetoGo repeatedly charged large amounts of money from my bank account over several months.
I never knowingly subscribed to any paid plan. I did not agree to recurring payments. At no point was there a transparent contract, explicit consent, or a clear confirmation that money would be withdrawn on a recurring basis.
When I tried to cancel the so-called “subscription” myself, I discovered something even more alarming:
there was no visible active subscription in my account at all.
No management panel. No cancellation option. Nothing.
Only after I confronted them directly and demanded an explanation did they suddenly “unsubscribe” me on their side — a clear indication that they knew exactly what they were doing.
This raises extremely serious questions:
How is it legal to withdraw money without explicit consent?
How is it allowed to hide subscriptions from users?
How can customers be charged without a clear opt-in or contract?
My conclusion is simple:
This is not an honest business model. This is a trap.
I strongly warn everyone:
Do not even log into their website or app.
The moment you interact with them, they somehow gain access to your payment details and start charging you.
This is misleading, unethical, and in my opinion borderline criminal.
I am shocked that such practices are tolerated.
Thieves, liars, and scammers hiding behind a polished interface.

Thieves, liars, and scammers hiding behind a polished interface.
